    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey im having some trouble with my deadlifts. every time i finish a set my lower back feels super tight and sore but i dont really feel it in my glutes or hamstrings like i should. what im doing wrong with my form?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your lower back pain and lack of glute activation suggest you are likely using your lumbar spine to move the bar rather than pushing through your posterior chain. Try placing a squat rack insert under the bar or using elbows to guide the weight's path to ensure your hips stay posterior during the pull. Consistently engaging your glutes at the start of each rep will help signal the muscles to do the work instead of absorbing the load through your lower back.",
      "source": "target",
