    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the tip. can u explain more about the spinal alignment part tho? like how exactly should my back look during the lift to make sure i'm not overcompensating with my spine?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "During a proper deadlift, your spine must remain in a neutral position throughout the movement, which means maintaining cortical arching while keeping your hips and shoulders stacked vertically. You should avoid overarching your lower back too much, as placing too much weight on the lumbar spine can cause it to become prone and painful. Instead, focus on rigidly extending your spine and letting your knees trail behind your hips so your body acts as a single pillar under the load rather than bending at the waist.",
      "source": "target",
