      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. how do i actually feel that \"pillar\" feeling you talked about? i feel like i'm just pulling with my arms and my backbone sometimes. is there a specific way to brace my core so it holds everything in place?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To feel that \"pillar\" sensation, visualize tightening your abdominal muscles as if someone is about to belt you, creating an internal cylinder of pressure that supports your spine before you pull. Instead of pulling with your arms, imagine driving your floor shoes downward into the earth while simultaneously pushing the floor away with your glutes, which activates the posterior chain to take the load. Consistently bracing your core during the static setup and rack pull phases is crucial to build the stability needed to transfer that force efficiently.",
